Dengue/dengue haemorrhagic fever in El Salvador - WHO Update
------------------------------------------------------------
As of 29 Jun 2002, the Ministry of Health of El Salvador has reported 1773
cases including 6 deaths of dengue infection. (see previous report:
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2002/june/21june2002.html>
All departments have been affected; based on overall rates, the worst
affected departments are San Salvador, Santa Ana, Cabanas, and Cuscatlan.
The WHO Fact sheet provides more information about dengue and dengue
haemorrhagic fever:
(<http://www.who.int/inf-fs/en/fact117.html>)
